Download and install Inkscape (https://inkscape.org/) or another vector graphics editor (e.g., Adobe Illustrator).

Windows/macOS: Install ``cmunrm.ttf'' and ``LiberationSans-Regular.'' One may need to install the fonts system-wide.
Linux: $ sudo apt install fonts-cmu ttf-mscorefonts-installer

Launch the vector graphics editor, and open each SVG file.

Edit each SVG file, then File > Export PNG Image... > 300 dpi or more > Export

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Optional

Substitute Times New Roman Italic for another font style, such as Liberation Serif Italic.
Windows/macOS: Install ``LiberationSerif-Italic.ttf.''
(Linux: Liberation Serif Italic is preinstalled.)